<h1>About This Project</h1>

<h2>Datasets Description</h2>

<p>
  This project uses two sets of data. The first comes from <a href="https://dog.ceo/dog-api">Dog CEO API.</a>
</p>
<p>
  The second data set is created using <a href="https://github.com/faker-ruby/faker">Faker.</a>
</p>
<p>
  There are four tables in this database. Dogs, Owners, Breeds, and SubBreeds. Each dog belongs to an owner
  and has a sub-breed. Each owner owns a dog. A subbreed belongs to a breed and a dog. Some breeds have sub-breeds.
</p>

<h3>Dogs Table</h3>
<p>The Dogs table stores information about individual dogs, including their breed, image, and ownership details.</p>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Column Name</th>
      <th>Type</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>id</td>
      <td>Integer</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>breed</td>
      <td>String</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>image_url</td>
      <td>String</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>sub_breed_id</td>
      <td>Integer</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>owner_id</td>
      <td>Integer</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h3>Owners Table</h3>
<p>The Owners table contains information about the owners of the dogs, including their names.</p>

<table>
